  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Unto the hearing of Augustus.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The title is the Greek equivalent, as seen in the name Sebaste (= Augusta) given to Samaria, for the epithet which, like our “his majesty,” had become a kind of official title of the Roman emperor. It had first been given by the Senate to Octavianus (Sueton. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Aug.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " c. 7), and was adopted by his successors. As connected with “augur, it had originally, like ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Sebastos, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "a religious connotation. The month of August, dedicated to the first emperor as July had been dedicated to Julius, and the names of Augsburg and Sebastopol, arc interesting as perpetuating its memory. The word for “hearing” (the same as our medical term ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "diagnosis",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") corresponds rather to our ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thorough investigation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
